# ✅ PART 2 — CHART TOOLTIP FIX (VERY IMPORTANT)

Fix tooltip inside "Leads by Status" donut chart.

## Current issues:
- Low contrast (dark on dark)
- No border / depth
- Bad readability
- Wrong positioning overlap

---

## Replace tooltip design with:

tooltip: {
  backgroundColor: "#111827",
  borderColor: "rgba(139,92,246,0.4)",
  borderWidth: 1,
  borderRadius: 8,
  padding: 10,
  textStyle: {
    color: "#ffffff",
    fontSize: 13,
    fontWeight: 500
  }
}

---

## Improve tooltip content format

Instead of:
"converted : 1"

Use:

formatter: (value, name) => {
  return `
    <div style="font-weight:600; margin-bottom:4px;">
      ${name}
    </div>
    <div style="color:#a78bfa;">
      ${value} leads
    </div>
  `;
}

---

## Add shadow for visibility

extraCssText: "box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);"

---

## Fix tooltip position (avoid clipping)

tooltip: {
  position: function (point, params, dom, rect, size) {
    return [
      point[0] + 10,
      point[1] - 40
    ];
  }
}

---

## Add hover emphasis (important UX)

emphasis: {
  itemStyle: {
    shadowBlur: 20,
    shadowColor: "rgba(139,92,246,0.5)"
  },
  scale: true
}

